The paper deals with the problem of testing convexity of functions over various discrete domains, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve combinatorial and information-theoretic arguments, which are typical of the sub-fields of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
